# Branch, PR, and release guardrails

Read also: `docs/contributing.md`, `docs/releasing.md`, `AGENTS.md`.

## Branch and main

- Default base: **`main`** (no `develop`).
- Before substantive work: branch from `main` — `feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, or `chore/` prefix.
- **Never** commit or push to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Never** merge, approve PRs, or run the release workflow unless explicitly asked.
- **Never** use destructive git (`push --force`, `reset --hard`) unless explicitly asked.
- Commits only when the user asks; otherwise leave changes uncommitted or on a feature branch.

## Commits

- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`, `ci:` (optional scope).
- Clear subject; body only when it adds context.

## Pre-PR / task completion (code changes)

```bash
npm run validate
```

Also when behavior changes:

- Update `CHANGELOG.md` → `## [Unreleased]`
- Update `docs/CURRENT_PRODUCT_SURFACE.md` if routes, APIs, or shipped status changed
- Add/update tests
- No secrets in git

Trivial docs-only edits may skip validate.

## Pull requests

- Open with `gh pr create` only when asked (summary + test plan).
- Prefer squash merge; address review on the same branch.

## Releases (manual only)

Invariant: `package.json` version **X.Y.Z** ⟺ tag **vX.Y.Z** ⟺ GitHub Release **vX.Y.Z**.

- **Do not** dispatch `.github/workflows/release.yml`, create tags, or publish releases without explicit user instruction.
- This repo does **not** publish to npm.
- Deploy (Vercel, etc.) is separate and manual.

## Version source

Canonical version: `package.json` → `"version"`.
